WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:01.369
Alright!

00:00:01.369 --> 00:00:03.950
Let's take your app from development to

00:00:03.950 --> 00:00:04.319
production.

00:00:04.319 --> 00:00:05.425
Three short steps,

00:00:05.425 --> 00:00:07.269
all driven from your laptop.

00:00:08.126 --> 00:00:10.686
During development you run the app from inside

00:00:10.686 --> 00:00:13.326
the repo, so it stops when you disconnect

00:00:14.046 --> 00:00:16.686
. In production you launch it from your laptop with

00:00:16.766 --> 00:00:19.726
the CLI, and it keeps running detached.

00:00:23.198 --> 00:00:25.358
Time to start the app in production mode from the

00:00:25.358 --> 00:00:27.998
laptop. The deploy command calls

00:00:27.998 --> 00:00:31.118
the same up function we used during development, but

00:00:31.118 --> 00:00:33.918
it runs detached. Close your laptop

00:00:33.998 --> 00:00:35.358
and the app keeps going.

00:00:38.304 --> 00:00:40.864
App running in production. Same command, same

00:00:40.864 --> 00:00:42.464
result, on the real server.

00:00:45.887 --> 00:00:48.927
Now enable autostart so the app survives

00:00:48.927 --> 00:00:51.567
a server reboot. From here on, if the

00:00:51.567 --> 00:00:54.287
server restarts, this repo comes back

00:00:54.367 --> 00:00:55.087
automatically.

00:00:57.541 --> 00:01:00.581
Autostart on. The app survives reboots.

00:01:04.064 --> 00:01:06.704
Let us list which repositories have autostart

00:01:06.704 --> 00:01:09.344
enabled. Confirms our app is in the boot list.

00:01:11.550 --> 00:01:13.230
There it is, in the boot list.

00:01:16.651 --> 00:01:19.371
And to stop the app, one command from the laptop

00:01:19.611 --> 00:01:22.251
. One command up, one command down. All

00:01:22.251 --> 00:01:23.131
from your terminal.

00:01:25.838 --> 00:01:27.838
Stopped. One command up, one command down.

00:01:28.856 --> 00:01:31.896
And that's production mode in a nutshell. See

00:01:31.896 --> 00:01:32.776
you in the next one!
